<item>
            <title>[LU-10170] OSP device could miss wakeup from committed sync</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10170</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the current implementation of &lt;tt&gt;osp_sync_add_rec()&lt;/tt&gt;, it adds the &lt;tt&gt;osp_device&lt;/tt&gt; into the wakeup list before inserting the actual record. However, if the OSP device is woken up and taken out of the list by a previous committed sync change, it will miss the wakeup for the recent sync change and then setattr RPC to OST would never be sent.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
